Install R on linux (centos/debian):
    eg. yum install R.3.5 ==> centos
    eg. R-3.5.1-win.ext   ==> Windows

Start R interpreter or gui:
    eg. # R            ==> R interpreter centos
    eg. # R --gui=tk   ==> R gui centos
    eg. R.exe          ==> R interpreter Windows
    eg. Rgui.exe       ==> R gui Windows

    From gui you can load R script file to execute.
    For some package dependency we may need to install packages 
    from R shell.
    > install.packages('plot')
